Scripts.Name: Apply MOP1, 2 and 3
Scripts.Script:
Imports Microsoft.VisualBasic
Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic
Imports System.IO
Imports System.Linq
Imports System.Windows.Forms
Imports SM64Lib
Imports DevComponents.DotNetBar
Imports Pilz.IO

Module Script

    Private Const MyMsgText As String =
"The More Object Patches has been optimized to work with SM64 ROM Manager ROMs, but they still are experimental because they break water in custom level e.g." & vbnewline & vbnewline &
"If you want to use water you can use it as normal, but the texture will be missing. So you have to place your own face with an water texture and with texture animation on."  & vbnewline & vbnewline &
"Are you sure you want to continue patching the More Object Patches on this ROM?"

    Sub Main(params as IReadOnlyDictionary(Of String, Object))
        If MessageBox.Show(MyMsgText, "More Object Patches", MessageBoxButtons.YesNo, MessageBoxIcon.Warning) = DialogResult.Yes Then
            Const ppfFileName = "mop123rm.ppf"
            Dim files As EmbeddedFilesContainer = params("files")
            Dim patchFile As String = files.GetLocalFilePath(ppfFileName)
            
            General.PatchClass.ApplyPPF(params("romfile"), patchFile)
            
            Dim rommgr as RomManager = params("rommgr")
            if rommgr isnot nothing andalso rommgr.GlobalBehaviorBank.Config.Enabled Then
                'Add changes to Global Behavior Bank
                '...
            End If
        End If
    End Sub

End Module

Scripts.Name: Open MOP Patcher
Scripts.Script:
Imports Microsoft.VisualBasic
Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic
Imports System.Diagnostics
Imports System.IO
Imports System.Linq
Imports System.Windows.Forms
Imports SM64Lib
Imports Pilz.IO

Module Script

    Sub Main(params as IReadOnlyDictionary(Of String, Object))
        Dim tweakDir as String = Path.GetDirectoryName(params("profilepath"))
        
        Const ppfFileName = "MOPPatcher.exe"
        Dim files As EmbeddedFilesContainer = params("files")
        Dim patchFile As String = files.GetLocalFilePath(ppfFileName)
        
        dim p as new Process
        p.StartInfo.Arguments       = """" & params("romfile") & """"
        p.StartInfo.FileName        = patchFile
        p.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = False
        p.Start
        p.WaitForExit
    End Sub

End Module
